fields.name: DeclarationsMessage
fields.fieldText:
IMPORTANT INSTRUCTIONS

You must be able to agree to the declaration statements in this application in order to proceed with the online renewal of your license.

If you CANNOT agree with, or are uncertain of how to respond to, any of the confirmation or declaration statements, please contact the NSCP for further instructions.

fields.name: NoActionsMessage
fields.fieldText: There are currently no actions for you to take with your registrations

fields.name: NoOrBlankResponseMessage
fields.fieldText:
You must be able to agree to all the declaration statements in this application in order to proceed with the online renewal of your license.


If you CANNOT agree with, or are uncertain of how to respond to, any of the confirmation or declaration statements, please contact the NSCP for further instruction.


Select "Previous" to go back to the previous screen and modify your answers.

Select "Finish" to exit the renewal application (your application responses will be saved).

fields.name: NotAllowedToRenewScreen
fields.fieldText: You may not renew at this time. Please check your account for an outstanding balance or contact NSCP for clarification.

fields.name: NotEnoughCEUsSelectedMessage
fields.fieldText: A minimum of 15 CE Units are required to renew your licence. Please click the Professional Development tab in the top right corner and enter your CEs in order to proceed with your licence renewal.

fields.name: MakeSureYouClickNextMessage
fields.fieldText:
Do Not Close The Page!

Please ensure you click the "Next" button once the green check mark appears.

Failure to do so may result in renewals being processed inaccurately.

fields.name: PaymentUnsuccessfulMessage
fields.fieldText: Sorry your payment was not successful please try again

fields.name: Copy_1_of_NoOrBlankResponseMessage
fields.fieldText:
You must be able to agree to the Practice Declaration statement in this application in order to proceed with the online renewal of your license.


If you CANNOT agree with, or are uncertain of how to respond to the Practice Declaration statements, please contact the NSCP for further instruction.


Select "Previous" to go back to the previous screen and modify your answers.

Select "Finish" to exit the renewal application (your application responses will be saved).

fields.name: PracticeHoursHeader
fields.fieldText: Practice Hours

fields.name: PracticeHoursDisclaimer
fields.fieldText:
The following declaration must be completed to renew as direct patient care: I declare that I have practiced sufficient direct patient care pharmacy in the two preceding years to the full scope of a licensed pharmacist or pharmacy technician (as applicable) to maintain the competence to practise direct patient care pharmacy.


If you cannot certify that you have practised sufficient direct patient care in the previous two years, your options for renewal of an active pharmacy license are (i) indirect patient care or (ii) nonpractising. You must contact the NSCP for further instructions on how to proceed with your licence renewal.

fields.name: UpdateEmploymentEducationInsuranceMessage
fields.fieldText:
Please ensure your employment, education, and insurance information is up-to-date.


If no edits are needed click next to proceed to declarations. If you make edits to the existing information in the table(s) below you will be presented with a review screen to confirm your edits prior to proceeding to the declarations.

fields.name: ReviewEmploymentHistoryInformation
fields.fieldText:
If your employment information has changed, please enter the end date. If your employment information is not listed please check the "Add Employment" box and fill out the required information. In order to add secondary employment information, you must first enter your primary employment information (even if it already exists in the table below).


Please carefully review your current employment information below.

If your employment information has not changed, no action is required.

fields.name: DateInfoScreen
fields.fieldText:
Entering start and end dates is not required. However, providing approximate start and end dates informs the NSCP of active employment. Practitioners are encouraged to maintain the accuracy of these dates.

When entering start and end dates use the calendar icon and select the date on the calendar to ensure correct formatting.
